    "slug": "intense-fog-weather",
    "description": "<p><strong>Intense Fog</strong> is something unparalleled, a truly oppressive and phobia-inducing soup that may cause one to struggle to even see their own hand in front of their face. This fog is so thick, you may even struggle to see silouettes in its walls. Predators and the clairvoyant are at their peak in these conditions.</p><p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Effects:</span></strong></p><ul><li>For the purposes of Abilities, Attacks, Perks, and Traits, this Weather is considered to also be “Foggy”.</li><li>Creatures without special forms of sight have -1 ACC on actions or attacks against creatures outside their Reach.</li><li>Electric-Type Attacks deal 60% less damage.</li><li>Creatures without special forms of sight are always considered to be in Rough Terrain and have their Attacks and Abilities lose [Friendly].</li><li>Bug-Type creatures possess High Cover against Ranged attacks and have their SPD increased by 50%.</li><li>Psychic-Type creatures have their SPATK and SPDEF stats increased by 40%.</li><li>Sleight of Hand and Stealth rolls gain +2 DoS, and Navigate and Spot rolls lose -2 DoS.</li></ul>"
  },
